      "translation": "and their families."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b13",
      "translation": "AIA has a long and distinguished history in Asia. Having successfully navigated various periods of social upheaval and uncertainty, we have earned an outstanding"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b14",
      "translation": "reputation that reflects our trustworthiness, resilience and commitment to doing the right thing for our stakeholders. Since early 2020, the COVID-19 pandemic has created a constantly evolving and increasingly complex business environment, with unprecedented shifts in political, macroeconomic and capital market conditions. In such an environment,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b15",
      "translation": "AIA's financial strength and our purpose of helping people live healthier, longer, better lives have become even more significant. I am deeply grateful to all AIA employees, agents and partners who, despite facing the most severe challenges, have cared for the community, fulfilled their duties and remained focused on providing support to our customers,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b16",
      "translation": "their families and our communities."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b17",
      "translation": "Due to the impact of COVID-19 control measures on new business sales, new business value declined to US$2.765 billion. We quickly adopted innovative digital tools to enhance operational efficiency, and with the recent relaxation of movement restrictions, sales momentum recovered strongly and continued into early 2021."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b18",
      "translation": "Compared with the same period last year, new business value in the first two months of 2021 grew by 15%."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b19",
      "translation": "Operating profit after tax increased by 5% to US$5.942 billion, while underlying free surplus generated rose by 7% to US$5.843 billion, reflecting the high quality of our recurring earnings sources. Embedded value equity reached a record high of US$67.2 billion. As at 31 December 2020, the Group's Local Capital Adequacy Ratio was"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b20",
      "translation": "374%, demonstrating our strong capital position and prudent financial management."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b21",
      "translation": "The Board recommends a final dividend of HK$1.0030 per share, an increase of 7.5%, reflecting the strength and resilience of our financial performance and the Board's continued confidence in the Group's future prospects. This brings the full year dividend for 2020 to HK$1.3530 per share. The Board continues to follow AIA's long-established prudent, sustainable"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "p10_b22",
      "translation": "and progressive dividend policy, enabling the Group to capture future growth opportunities while maintaining financial flexibility."
